China's Wang Yilyu/Huang Dongping outplayed compatriots Ou Xuanyi/Huang Yaqiong 2-0 to take the 2022 South Korea Masters mixed doubles title on Sunday. Shortly after the women's singles, China's He Bingjiao defeated compatriot and Olympic champion Chen Yufei 2-1 in the other all-Chinese final on Sunday, as He took her second victory of the season 21-14, 14-21, 21-9. Earlier in March, He defeated Chen in the German Open women's singles final 2-0. Team China registered four pairs in the mixed doubles event in this tournament, while three pairs entered the last eight. In the mixed doubles final, Olympic champions Wang/Huang exhibited stronger skills than the other pair on some of the key points and took the victory 21-17, 21-17. (With input from Xinhua News Agency)